BUSINESS AT A GLANCE
( lb ) c.1998 N.Y .
Times News Service
GOLDMAN , SACHS CONSIDERS SELLING SHARES TO PUBLIC
Jon Corzine , senior partner at Goldman , Sachs & AMP ; Co. , told employees that management was considering options for the firm 's future , including taking the Wall Street firm public .
Goldman , Sachs ' partners have pondered going public several times before , but the changes now sweeping the financial-services industry have made the current discussion more urgent .
SLOWDOWN IN MANUFACTURING SEEN
The National Association of Purchasing Management 's index declined to 51.4 last month from 52.9 in April as exports faltered and cheap imports pressured factory profits .
In another economic report , construction spending rose 0.8 percent in April , to $ 630.1 billion .
NASDAQ FALLS 1.8 PERCENT , BUT DOW RISES
Intel , which fell to a 52-week low , led technology issues down .
The technology-heavy Nasdaq fell 1.8 percent , to 1 , 746.82 .
The Dow Jones industrial average rose as investors sought a safe haven from the turmoil in Asia and Russia .
The Dow climbed 22.42 points , to 8 , 922.37 .
The Standard & AMP ; Poor 's 500 index was little changed .
Treasury prices rose .
The yield on the benchmark 30-year Treasury bond declined to 5.77 percent , from 5.80 percent on Friday .
A PLAN TO ACCOUNT FOR DERIVATIVES
The United States ' accounting rule makers have approved a proposal that will force companies to record the value of derivatives in their financial statements .
RUSSIAN STOCK MARKET PLUMMETS
Russia 's financial crisis worsened .
The Russian stock market fell more than 10 percent ; there were signs of strain among banks , and Russia 's stock futures market suspended trading .
JAPAN KEY TO ASIAN RECOVERY
Deputy Treasury Secretary Lawrence Summers said that the health and direction of the Japanese economy was an important factor in the Asian recovery .
TRAVELERS CONFIRMS STAKE IN NIKKO
As expected , Travelers Group will acquire a 25 percent stake in Nikko Securities , Japan 's third-largest securities firm , for $ 1.6 billion .
The announcement of the deal raised questions about how quickly the Japanese financial industry would consolidate .
OVITZ FACES MAJOR FISCAL CHALLENGE
Michael Ovitz , who was ousted as president of Walt Disney , faces major challenges when he takes over Livent this week .
Livent , the producer of recent Broadway musicals like `` Ragtime '' and `` Kiss of the Spider Woman , '' and the only publicly held company whose primary business is live theater production , has lost $ 50 million in the last 15 months .
WIRELESS PHONE CROSSES CONTINENTS
Audiovox and Bosch Telecom have developed a wireless phone that can operate on different continents without modification .
FDA APPROVES HIV URINE TEST
The FDA approved marketing of Calypte Biomedical 's urine test for HIV .
The test is the first complete urine-based diagnostic kit for HIV that does not require confirmation by blood test .
